{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>RNA cyclases are a family of RNA-modifying enzymes that are conserved in eukaryotes, bacteria and archaea. Type 1 RNA 3'-terminal phosphate cyclases ([ec:6.5.1.4]) [[cite:PUB00001300], [cite:PUB00003565]] catalyse the conversion of 3'-phosphate to a 2',3'-cyclic phosphodiester at the end of RNA:</p>\n\n<p><reaction>\nATP + RNA 3'-terminal-phosphate = AMP + diphosphate + RNA terminal-2',3'-cyclic-phosphate\n</reaction></p>\n\n<p>The physiological function of the cyclase is not known, but the enzyme could be involved in the maintenance of cyclic ends in tRNA splicing intermediates or in the cyclisation of the 3' end of U6 snRNA [[cite:PUB00001300]].</p>\n\n<p>A second subfamily of RNA 3'-terminal phosphate cyclases (type 2) that do not have cyclase activity have been identified in eukaryotes. They are localised to the nucleolus and are involved in ribosomal modification [[cite:PUB00042947]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "4o89", "name" "Crystal structure of RtcA, the RNA 3'-terminal phosphate cyclase from Pyrococcus horikoshii."}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR013792", "name" "RNA 3'-terminal phosphate cyclase/enolpyruvate transferase, alpha/beta", "type" "homologous_superfamily"} {"accession" "IPR036553", "name" "RNA 3'-terminal phosphate cyclase, insert domain superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"} {"accession" "IPR037136", "name" "RNA 3'-terminal phosphate cyclase domain superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"pirsf" {"PIRSF005378" "RNA 3'-terminal phosphate cyclase"}, "panther" {"PTHR11096" "RNA 3' TERMINAL PHOSPHATE CYCLASE"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "RNA 3'-terminal phosphate cyclase", "short" "RNA3'_term_phos_cyc"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 48, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 3346, "taxa" 13776, "subfamilies" 0, "intera